<section class="section section--alt" id="qb-help-speak-expert-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">A Certified ProAdvisor answers &mdash; not a script.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The person you speak to is a Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications &mdash; someone who works inside QuickBooks files for a living, not a tier-one agent reading from a flowchart. They&rsquo;ll listen to what&rsquo;s going on, ask the questions that actually matter for your file, and tell you honestly whether this is something to fix, something to leave alone, or something that belongs with Intuit. If there&rsquo;s real work to do, you get a written, fixed-fee scope before anyone touches the books &mdash; no open-ended hourly meter. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not QuickBooks product support; an Intuit account, login, or billing matter stays with Intuit.</p>
    </div>
